The paper discusses a digital forensic framework for smart environments, which involves analyzing data generated by IoT devices and sensors. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR), as the framework aims to hold those violating security policies accountable. The paper also involves data processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the storage and retrieval of data, which is relevant to database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the potential privacy concerns of smart environments, which could fall under the category of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY).
